    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Diesel Engine Diagnostic Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Engine Systems - Engine
        Identification - Engine Emission Label
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Engine Emission Label</title>
        <para>A common emission label is issued for the International&#174; DT 466 and DT 570 diesel engines.</para>
        <figure id="f2700102" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH34/H34005.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Engine emission label (Example)</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) emission label is on top of the valve cover. The engine label
            includes the following:
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Model year</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Engine family, model, and displacement</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Advertised brake horsepower and torque rating</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Emission family and control systems</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>U.S. Family Emission Limits (FEL), if applicable</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Valve lash specifications</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Engine serial number</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>EPA, EURO, and reserved fields for specific applications</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <para>
            <title>Engine Accessories</title>
        </para>
        <para>The following engine accessories may have manufacturer's labels or identification plates:</para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Air compressor (for brake or suspension system)</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Air conditioning compressor</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Alternator</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Cooling fan clutch</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>EVRT&#174; electronically controlled turbocharger - International's version of a Variable Geometry
                    Turbocharger (VGT)
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Power steering pump</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Starter motor</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <para>Labels or identification plates include information and specifications helpful to vehicle operators and
            technicians.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
